Creating, Modifying, and Deleting Control Panel Groups #!N #!EC #!N #!N 
The following describes how to create Control Panel groups, restrict access 
(build hierarchies), and specify which Control Panels are open at startup. 
#!N #!N Control panel groups are created using the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control 
Panel Group... #!EF dialog box. The dialog box is opened by 
selecting the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Control Panel Groups... #!EF option under the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   
Options #!EF menu in the VPE window (  #!Lppromx83,dxall405 f Figure 83  #!EL  ). #!Cbrown 
#!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*    #!Rppromx83 #!N Graphics omitted from Online Documentation. Please see 
the manual. #!N #!N Figure 83. Control Panel Group Dialog Box 
#!EF #!N #!EC #!N #!N The right side of the dialog 
displays the list of Control Panels. Associated with each Control Panel 
is a toggle button to the left and an ellipsis toggle 
to the right. The left side of the dialog is a 
list of the existing groups. This list remains empty until a 
group is created. At the bottom of the dialog box is 
a series of pushbuttons that are used for creating, modifying, and 
deleting groups. Clicking on the ellipsis causes the corresponding Control Panel 
to be opened (or raised to the front if it is 
already opened). Clicking on the ellipsis when it is depressed closes 
the corresponding Control Panel and releases the toggle. #!N #!N To 
create a Control Panel group: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N 
#!I30 #!N 1. Select the Control Panels that you want in 
the group by activating the corresponding left toggle button. #!N #!I30 
#!N 2. Enter the name of the group in the text 
field next to  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Group Name #!EF Although it is not 
required, select a name that is unique compared to the names 
of other Control Panels or other groups. #!N #!I30 #!N 3. 
Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Add #!EF pushbutton at the bottom of 
the dialog box. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N The 
new group is added to the list of groups displayed on 
the left side of the dialog box. The group is also 
added to the list of named Control Panels that is displayed 
by the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Open Control Panel by Name #!EF option in 
the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Windows #!EF menu. #!N #!N Once a Control Panel 
group is created, it can be modified. Modifying a Control Panel 
group can include changing its name, adding new Control Panels, and 
removing Control Panels from the group. #!N #!N To modify a 
Control Panel group: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N #!I30 #!N 
1. Click on the Control Panel group name that is to 
be modified. This causes the name of the Control Panel group 
to be displayed in the group name text field and causes 
the toggle buttons of the Control Panels that are members of 
the group to be activated. All other Control Panel buttons are 
released. #!N #!I30 #!N 2. You may now change the name 
of the group by editing the text field. Add a new 
Control Panel by clicking on its toggle button (this causes the 
toggle button to be activated). To remove a Control Panel from 
the group, click on its toggle button to release it. #!N 
#!I30 #!N 3. Once you have made the desired changes to 
the Control Panel group, click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Modify #!EF button 
at the bottom of the dialog box. This causes the change 
to take effect. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF #!N #!N #!N To 
delete a Control Panel group: #!N #!I0 #!N  #!F-adobe-times-medium-r-normal--18*   #!N #!N 
#!I30 #!N 1. Select the group by clicking on its name. 
#!N #!I30 #!N 2. Click on the  #!F-adobe-times-bold-r-normal--18*   Delete #!EF button 
at the bottom of the dialog box. #!N #!I0 #!N #!EF 
